2456fd3a-e6c3-4d4c-b015-68151b9bc1a1.0cded468-3a5a-474c-8d4a-11916fa16fa5.prompt=66e936fc-5723-4377-955d-6f0f3a27ec41.f478ea30-073c-4c2c-93f9-7b6f34a3419d.prompt 2456fd3a-e6c3-4d4c-b015-68151b9bc1a1.0d13a320-1590-4af2-b7bf-d70590f6b501.prompt=User Identifier 2456fd3a-e6c3-4d4c-b015-68151b9bc1a1.130c2fc9-75cb-4454-827f-50e0c599b441.description=
Imports a Windows 2008 R2 virtual machine from VmWare 4.1.0 to the given Amazon account. This flow checks if all preconditions are met and if not it automatically sets the desired state on the target machine. In case you want to return to your initial settings it is recommended that you previously create a snapshot of the machine before running this operation. 

Inputs\:
    path - The path to the location where to export the VMDK file of the target machine. 
    username - The username for the imported virtual machine.
    password - The password for the imported virtual machine.
    vmHost -  VMware vCenter, ESX or ESXi host hostname or IP.
    vmUser - VMware username.
    vmPassword - VMware user's password.
    vmIdentifierType - Virtual machine identifier type.  
Valid values\: "inventorypath", "name", "ip", "hostname", "uuid", "vmid"
    virtualMachine - Primary Virtual Machine identifier. Inventorypath (Datacenter/vm/Folder/MyVM), Name of VM, IP (IPv4 or IPv6 depending upon ESX version), hostname (full), UUID, or the VM id (vm-123,123).
    rasHost - Hostname or ip address of the machine where you have installed the EC2 API Tools. It is recommended to use localhost.
    rasPort - Port number for connecting to the rasHost.
    rasUsername - Username for connecting to the rasHost.
    rasPassword - Password for connecting to the rasHost.
    protocol -  The protocol used to run the Amazon Import Instance command.
Valid values\: ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, REXEC, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, or HPOM
    instanceType - The type of instance to be launched.
Valid Values\: m1.small | m1.large | m1.xlarge | c1.medium | c1.xlarge | m2.xlarge | m2.2xlarge | m2.4xlarge
Default\: m1.medium
    architecture - The architecture of the image.
Valid values\: i386 | x86_64
    s3BucketName - The Amazon S3 destination bucket for the manifest.
    accessKeyId - Access key ID of the bucket owner.
    accessKey - The secret access key of the bucket owner.
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to connect to Amazon.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port. You must either specify values for both  and  inputs or leave them both empty.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    serviceEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
    securityToken - The security token that you must pass to use the temporary credentials. You can generate this by using operations from the Security Token Service folder. You can only use the token together with the temporary credentials generated by the same operations.
    deleteCreatedFiles - Specifies whether to delete the files generated by the OVF Export operation.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    statusFlowPath - The path to the flow that checks the status of the Import conversion task and cleans the results.
Default value\:  Library/Integrations/Amazon/EC2/VM Import/VMWare Windows Server 2008 Vm Import/Check Import Status

Results\:
    taskId- The Conversion Task Id created when importing the virtual machine into Amazon.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. 
Notes\:
1. In order to use this operation you need to download & install the Amazon EC2 API Tools. You can find them at\: http\://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/SettingUp_CommandLine.html 
2. Please note that this operation includes also a schedule for the Check Import Status flow. Adapt the inputs of the scheduler to fit your own settings.

This workflow returns the list of Artifact’s Properties and values.

Inputs-
artifactId  –  Artifact id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
propertyNames – List of property names separated by pipe |
If user provides this inputs, flow will return the values for given property names only. Otherwise flow will return all properties and values for the given artifact.
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
deleteCreatedFiles
ec2ToolsDir
exportPath
instanceType
platform
s3BucketName
